td.paragraph: The patient continues to tolerate Semaglutide 2 mg well and has demonstrated adherence to lifestyle modifications, including dietary changes with caloric restriction. We will continue the current regimen, as it has proven effective in maintaining weight control without adverse effects. On today's visit, Semaglutide 2 mg was administered SC to the left abdomen without complications. She understands the long-term side-effects of Semaglutide are not well known. She also understands the need to maintain ongoing caloric deficit for optimal weight reduction as well as maintaining adequate hydration and protein intake. We reviewed and discussed results of her prior laboratory results revealing LDL of 131, creatinine of 0.60, A1c of 5.2. We advised her to decrease her intake of fried fatty foods for management of her elevated LDL. All questions and concerns were answered and addressed and a heart-healthy diet and lifestyle was encouraged and endorsed. She is to follow-up in 1 week or sooner should new symptoms arise. She agrees to plan of care.
